 # Changelog
 
+## 2026-07-17 Australia/Sydney - ADP V0.1 task ADP-S6-P01-T070 (Dataset Snapshot + observed_at leakage guard; NOT_DEPLOYED)
+
+- Seventieth task of the ADP V0.1 FINAL EXECUTION program (S6-P01). Ensures 2026-backfilled old files cannot pretend to have been known at a historical point in time: a dataset snapshot is keyed on observed_at (when ADP actually fetched a document), never on doc_date (when the policy issued), so a 2016 policy observed only in 2026 is not in a 2018 snapshot. release_mode NOT_DEPLOYED; a read-only library, the production worker/cron/data untouched. New tool arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/tools/dataset_snapshot.py: snapshot(corpus, as_of) (docs with observed_at <= as_of, malformed/missing observed_at excluded, deterministic order + reproducible snapshot_id), assert_no_leakage(dataset, as_of) (raises LeakageError if any doc was observed after as_of or has an unverifiable observed_at -- the tripwire), and rebuild_for_prediction (reproduce the exact as-of dataset for a prediction's origin_date). Reuses T056 coverage_asof._parse_date. Deliverables under arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/evidence/ADP-S6-P01-T070/: dataset_snapshot_report.json, known_gaps.md, and adversarial_review.md (review CONFIRMED_SOUND). Acceptance verified (evidence/ADP-S6-P01-T070/test-results/dataset_snapshot_tests.txt, ACCEPTANCE = PASS, exit 0): a clean as-of snapshot passes the leakage guard, while EXTERNALLY injecting a future-observed doc, a 2026-backfilled doc, or a doc with no observed_at each RAISES (so injecting a future document makes the test fail); the snapshot is observed_at-keyed, not doc_date-keyed (a backfilled doc whose doc_date 2016-05-01 is before the 2018 as_of but whose observed_at is 2026-07-01 is excluded, so the 2018 snapshot is exactly [a, b]); and any prediction can rebuild its dataset (rebuild_for_prediction reproduces the snapshot_id, is order-independent and reproducible, and a later as_of expands the dataset). Realtime not regressed (no deploy, live build b189d3cc0703 == T040). Cost (unknown != 0): production new_requests 0, D1 0, R2 0, model_calls 0. Ends IMPLEMENTATION_READY_FOR_INDEPENDENT_VERIFICATION.
+
 ## 2026-07-17 Australia/Sydney - ADP V0.1 task ADP-S6-P01-T069 (prediction target catalog + Outcome Rule + event labels; NOT_DEPLOYED)
 
 - Sixty-ninth task of the ADP V0.1 FINAL EXECUTION program -- opens Stage S6 (Prediction & Backtest). Defines what counts as 'happened' BEFORE training any model: a prediction target is admissible only if it can be settled objectively (0/1) by FUTURE OFFICIAL evidence (A0/A1 original text) via an unambiguous rule; a vague/subjective target is rejected and may not enter the backtest. release_mode NOT_DEPLOYED; a read-only library of deterministic settlement rules (NOT a trained model, so MODEL_SPEC/formula unchanged), the production worker/cron/data untouched. New tool arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/tools/prediction_targets.py: make_target, SETTLEMENT_TYPES (official_doc_exists / status_transition / count_at_least), is_settleable (known objective predicate + all required non-empty fields + a finite positive horizon), admit_targets (admitted vs rejected-with-reason), settle (settles against OFFICIAL evidence within [origin, origin+horizon]; a definite 0/1 or 'pending' if the window has not elapsed; ignores media and out-of-window observations so the future cannot leak; raises on a non-settleable target). Deliverables under arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/evidence/ADP-S6-P01-T069/: prediction_targets_report.json, known_gaps.md, and adversarial_review.md (review CONFIRMED_SOUND). Acceptance verified (evidence/ADP-S6-P01-T069/test-results/prediction_targets_tests.txt, ACCEPTANCE = PASS, exit 0): every admitted target (G1 official_doc_exists, G2 count_at_least, G3 status_transition) is settleable and settles to a definite label (official match 1 / media-or-future-only 0 / two releases 1 / one 0 / revoked 1 / unelapsed window pending); three ambiguous targets (a subjective predicate, an empty required field, a zero horizon) are rejected and settle() refuses each so they cannot be backtested; and settlement is official-only with a leak-proof observed_at window -- a media look-alike does not settle, a future-observed official match does not leak (in-window 1 / after-window 0 / exactly-on-end 1 / one-day-after not leaked / malformed observed_at safe). Realtime not regressed (no deploy, live build b189d3cc0703 == T040). Cost (unknown != 0): production new_requests 0, D1 0, R2 0, model_calls 0. Ends IMPLEMENTATION_READY_FOR_INDEPENDENT_VERIFICATION.
